               <head>Letters of Emperor 'Alamgir by 'Inayatullah Kashmiri</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kalimāt-i ṭayyibāt by Shaykh ʿInāyat Allāh Kanbūh</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129379 http://lccn.loc.gov/n2013007835" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_479-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656431.0x000001 viaf_17950016">Shaykh ʿInāyat Allāh Kanbūh</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656431.0x000001 viaf_17950016">عنايت الله </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3295">Kalimāt-i ṭayyibāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_3295">كلمات طيّبات</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of royal orders (tawqīʿāt) and notes of the Timurid or Mughal <persName key="viaf_6178410" role="aut">Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I</persName> (<persName key="viaf_6178410" role="aut">Aurangzeb</persName>) compiled after his death by the minister <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656431.0x000001 viaf_17950016" role="com">Shaykh ʿInāyat Allāh Khān Kashmīrī ibn Shukr Allāh</persName> (d. 1139/1726-7) at the behest of <persName key="viaf_314901452" role="pat">Emperor Bahādur Shāh I</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was completed, according to a couplet recording the chronogrammatic title <title>Kalimāt-i ṭayyibāt</title>, in 1121/1709 
                        </p>
                        <p>Well-written nastaʿlīq </p>
                        <p>Some folios are damaged </p>
                        <p>Not dated; circa eighteenth century </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
